byline.contributor: James Kanter contributed reporting from Brussels, and Dimitris Bounias from Athens.

abstract: Greek Parliament approves second package of policy changes its creditors say must be in place before bailout negotiations can begin; package, which includes overhauling banking and judicial systems, passed without large support from Prime Min Alexis Tsipras' leftist Syriza party, showing there is widening rift within.
lead_paragraph: Parliament approved a package of financial and judicial changes to keep negotiations on track for the bailout of about $94 billion.

headline.main: Greece Approves Second Set of Changes Needed for Bailout
headline.print_headline: Greek Leaders Approve Second Set of Changes Sought by Creditors

snippet: Parliament approved a package of financial and judicial changes to keep negotiations on track for the bailout of about $94 billion.
